      "Text": "[llm] system: %buildGoalPrompt%\n        user: %goalForLlm%\n         scheme: {\n            errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n            warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n            steps: [{index: int, approved?: bool, rebuildReason?: string, needsDetail?: bool,\n                  errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                  warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                  cache?: {durationSeconds: long, sliding?: bool, key?: string},\n                  onError?: {ignoreError?: bool, goal?: {name: string}, retryCount?: int, retryOverSeconds?: int, order?: string, message?: string},\n                  actions?: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}], return?: [{name: string}],\n                              errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                              warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}]}]}]\n                }\n        on error HandleBuildGoalFailure\n        write to %stepResults%",
      "Comment": null,
      "ModuleType": "PLang.Modules.LlmModule",
      "Name": "call_llm_with_structured_prompt_and_error_handling",
      "Description": "Invoke the language model module with a system prompt from %buildGoalPrompt% and a user prompt from %goalForLlm%, expecting a structured JSON response matching the provided schema that includes errors, warnings, steps, and actions. If an error occurs, handle it with the HandleBuildGoalFailure goal. The result of the LLM call is written to the %stepResults% variable.",
      "PrFileName": "07. call_llm_with_structured_prompt_and_error_handling.pr",
