  "SubGoals": [
    ".build\\BuildGoal\\HandleBuildGoalFailure\\00. Goal.pr"
  ],
  "Description": "The BuildGoal function is designed to construct a goal by executing a series of steps. It begins by logging the name of the goal being built. It retrieves all actions and type information, rendering templates for action summaries and goal formats for LLM. It loads a prompt from a file and interacts with the LLM system using this prompt and the formatted goal. The function handles potential errors and processes the results of the steps, applying each step in the results. Finally, it saves the constructed goal.",
